1. Active reactor mass balance (CSTR, flow $(1-f_b)v_0$, volume $V_a=(1-f_d)V$):  
$$ (1-f_b)v_0(C_{A0}-C_{Aa}) \;=\; V_a\,k\,C_{Aa} 
   \;=\;(1-f_d)V\,k\,C_{Aa}\,. $$  
2. Divide by $v_0$:  
$$ (1-f_b)(C_{A0}-C_{Aa}) \;=\;(1-f_d)\tau\,k\,C_{Aa}\,. $$  
3. Solve for $C_{Aa}$:  
$$ (1-f_b)C_{A0}
   =\bigl[(1-f_b)+(1-f_d)\,\tau k\bigr]\,C_{Aa}
   \;\Longrightarrow\;
   C_{Aa}
   =\frac{(1-f_b)\,C_{A0}}{(1-f_b)+(1-f_d)\,\tau k}\,. $$  
4. Final outlet mixes bypass and active streams:  
$$ C_A
   =(1-f_b)C_{Aa}+f_b\,C_{A0}
   =C_{A0}\Bigl[\frac{(1-f_b)^2}{(1-f_b)+(1-f_d)\tau k}+f_b\Bigr]\,. $$  
5. Engineerâ€™s model:  
$$ \frac{C_A}{C_{A0}}
   =\frac{1}{1+k_{\rm app}\,\tau}
   =f_b+\frac{(1-f_b)^2}{(1-f_b)+(1-f_d)\tau k}\,. $$  
6. Combine into single fraction:  
$$ f_b+\frac{(1-f_b)^2}{(1-f_b)+(1-f_d)\tau k}
   =\frac{(1-f_b)+f_b(1-f_d)\tau k}{(1-f_b)+(1-f_d)\tau k}\,. $$  
7. Hence  
$$ 1+k_{\rm app}\tau
   =\frac{(1-f_b)+(1-f_d)\tau k}{(1-f_b)+f_b(1-f_d)\tau k}
   \;\Longrightarrow\;
   k_{\rm app}\tau
   =\frac{(1-f_b)(1-f_d)\tau k}{(1-f_b)+f_b(1-f_d)\tau k}\,. $$  
8. Divide by $\tau$:  
$$ \boxed{k_{\rm app}
   =\frac{(1-f_b)(1-f_d)\,k}{(1-f_b)+f_b(1-f_d)\,k\,\tau}}\,. $$
